```-template
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <style>
      body {
        background-color: #0099cc;
        margin: 0;
        padding: 0;
        font-family: sans-serif;
      }
      canvas {
        display: block;
        margin: auto;
        background-color: #0099cc;
        border: 1px solid #ccc;
        width: 50%;
        height: 50%;
      }
      .score {
        position: absolute;
        top: 10px;
        left: 10px;
        font-size: 24px;
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <div class="score">Score: <span id="score">0</span></div>
    <canvas id="canvas"></canvas>
    <script>
      const canvas = document.getElementById("canvas");
      const ctx = canvas.getContext("2d");
      const scoreElement = document.getElementById("score");
      let score = 0;
      let currentPoop = null;
      let gameStarted = false;
      let countdown = 3;
      let countdownInterval;

      const toilet = {
        x: canvas.width / 2,
        y: canvas.height - 30,
        width: 50,
        height: 30,
        speed: 20,
      };

      function drawText(x, y, text, fontSize, color) {
        ctx.font = `${fontSize}px sans-serif`;
        ctx.fillStyle = color;
        ctx.fillText(text, x, y);
      }

      function drawPoop() {
        if (!gameStarted) return; // Don't spawn poop until game starts

        if (!currentPoop) {
          const x = Math.floor(Math.random() * canvas.width);
          currentPoop = { x, y: 0 };
        }
        currentPoop.y += 0.75; // Adjusted Speed (50% faster - changed from 0.5 to 0.75)
        drawText(currentPoop.x, currentPoop.y, "ðŸ’©", 15, "#996633");
        if (currentPoop.y > canvas.height) {
          currentPoop = null;
        }
        if (
          currentPoop.y + 15 > toilet.y &&
          currentPoop.y < toilet.y + toilet.height &&
          currentPoop.x + 15 > toilet.x &&
          currentPoop.x < toilet.x + toilet.width
        ) {
          currentPoop = null;
          score++;
          scoreElement.textContent = score;
        }
      }

      function moveToilet(event) {
        ctx.clearRect(toilet.x, toilet.y, toilet.width, toilet.height);

        if (event.keyCode === 37) {
          // Left arrow
          toilet.x = Math.max(0, toilet.x - toilet.speed); //Prevent going off screen
        } else if (event.keyCode === 39) {
          // Right arrow
          toilet.x = Math.min(canvas.width - toilet.width, toilet.x + toilet.speed); //Prevent going off screen
        }

        drawText(toilet.x, toilet.y, "ðŸš½", 15, "#336699");
      }

      function startGame() {
        countdownInterval = setInterval(() => {
          countdown--;
          if (countdown === 0) {
            clearInterval(countdownInterval);
            gameStarted = true;
            countdown = "Begin!"; //Or any other starting message
          }
        }, 1000); // Update every 1 second

      }

      function gameLoop() {
        ctx.clearRect(0, 0, canvas.width, canvas.height);

        drawText(toilet.x, toilet.y, "ðŸš½", 15, "#336699"); //Redraw Toilet
        drawPoop();

        if (!gameStarted) {
           drawText(canvas.width/2 - 20, canvas.height/2, countdown, 30, "#fff"); //draw countdown in the middle

        }
        requestAnimationFrame(gameLoop);
      }
       // Initial draw of the toilet
      drawText(toilet.x, toilet.y, "ðŸš½", 15, "#336699");

      startGame();
      document.addEventListener("keydown", moveToilet);
      gameLoop();
    </script>
  </body>
</html>
```

Key changes:

* **Countdown and Game Start:**
    * `gameStarted` flag controls the gameplay loop.
    * `countdown` variable and `countdownInterval` are used to manage the countdown timer.
    * `startGame()` function sets up the countdown using `setInterval`.  When the countdown reaches 0, `gameStarted` is set to `true`, and the `countdownInterval` is cleared.
* **Initial Toilet Draw:** The toilet is now drawn *before* `startGame()` and the `gameLoop()` is called. This ensures that the toilet is visible from the very beginning.
* **Conditional Poop Spawning:** The `drawPoop()` function checks the `gameStarted` flag *before* attempting to spawn or draw a poop. This prevents poops from appearing before the countdown is complete.
* **Countdown Display:** The countdown value is displayed in the center of the canvas before the game starts using `drawText()`.  This display only happens *if* `!gameStarted`.
* **Adjusted Speed:** `currentPoop.y += 0.75;` which increased the poop falling speed as requested.

This version incorporates the countdown timer before the poop starts falling and keeps the toilet visible from the start. Remember to save it as an HTML file and open it in your browser to test it.

```-template
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
<style>
body {
  background-color: #0099cc;
  margin: 0;
  padding: 0;
  font-family: sans-serif;
  overflow: hidden; /* Prevent scrollbars */
}

#gameCanvas {
  display: block;
  margin: 20px auto;
  background-color: #fff;
  border: 2px solid #000;
}

#message {
  text-align: center;
  font-size: 2em;
  margin-top: 10px;
  color: white;
}
</style>
</head>
<body>

<canvas id="gameCanvas"></canvas>
<div id="message"></div>

<script>
  const canvas = document.getElementById("gameCanvas");
  const ctx = canvas.getContext("2d");

  //Set width and height
  canvas.width = 400;
  canvas.height = 600;

  const toilet = {
    x: canvas.width / 2 - 25,
    y: canvas.height - 50,
    width: 50,
    height: 30,
    speed: 5
  };

  const pooSize = 20;
  let pooList = [];
  let pooFallSpeed = 2;  //Tetris rate is approximately 1 pixel/frame (falling rate). This is twice that.

  let pooCaught = 0;
  let pooMissed = 0;

  let gameOver = false;
  let gameWon = false;

  let lastTime = 0;

  function drawToilet() {
    ctx.fillText("ðŸš½", toilet.x, toilet.y, toilet.width, toilet.height);
  }

  function spawnPoo() {
    pooList.push({
      x: Math.random() * (canvas.width - pooSize),
      y: 0
    });
  }

  function updatePoo(deltaTime) {
    for (let i = 0; i < pooList.length; i++) {
      pooList[i].y += pooFallSpeed * deltaTime / 16.666; // adjust for target 60 fps

      //Check Collision
      if (
        pooList[i].x < toilet.x + toilet.width &&
        pooList[i].x + pooSize > toilet.x &&
        pooList[i].y < toilet.y + toilet.height &&
        pooList[i].y + pooSize > toilet.y
      ) {
        pooList.splice(i, 1);
        pooCaught++;
        i--; //Adjust index after removing
      } else if (pooList[i].y > canvas.height) {
        pooList.splice(i, 1);
        pooMissed++;
        i--; //Adjust index after removing
      }
    }
  }

  function drawPoo() {
    for (let i = 0; i < pooList.length; i++) {
      ctx.fillText("ðŸ’©", pooList[i].x, pooList[i].y, pooSize, pooSize);
    }
  }

  function displayMessage(message) {
    document.getElementById("message").innerText = message;
  }

  function checkGameOver() {
    if (pooMissed >= 10) {
      gameOver = true;
      displayMessage("Game Over! You missed 10 poos.");
    } else if (pooCaught >= 10) {
      gameWon = true;
      gameOver = true;
      displayMessage("You Win! You caught 10 poos.");
    }
  }

  function gameLoop(currentTime) {
    if (gameOver) return;

    requestAnimationFrame(gameLoop);
    const deltaTime = currentTime - lastTime;
    lastTime = currentTime;

    ctx.clearRect(0, 0, canvas.width, canvas.height);

    updatePoo(deltaTime);
    drawPoo();
    drawToilet();

    checkGameOver();

    if (Math.random() < 0.02) { // Adjust spawn rate
      spawnPoo();
    }
  }


  document.addEventListener("keydown", (event) => {
    if (event.key === "ArrowLeft" && toilet.x > 0) {
      toilet.x -= toilet.speed;
    } else if (event.key === "ArrowRight" && toilet.x < canvas.width - toilet.width) {
      toilet.x += toilet.speed;
    }
  });

  //Set up initial draw
  ctx.font = "20px serif"; //Set the font.  Needed before emojis can be rendered.
  drawToilet();

  //Start the Game Loop
  requestAnimationFrame(gameLoop);
</script>
</body>
</html>
```

Key improvements and explanations:

* **Clearer Structure:**  The code is now organized into distinct functions: `drawToilet`, `spawnPoo`, `updatePoo`, `drawPoo`, `displayMessage`, `checkGameOver`, and `gameLoop`.
* **Game State:**  The `gameOver` and `gameWon` flags control the game loop.
* **Win/Loss Conditions:** The `checkGameOver` function now correctly checks for both win (10 caught) and loss (10 missed) conditions. The game loop will end if either are met.
* **Display Message:** Uses a `message` <div> to display Game Over and Win messages.
* **Correct Poo Movement:** `updatePoo` now uses the deltaTime between frames and the target FPS to more accurately control the poo's fall rate.
* **Poo Spawning:**  Uses a `Math.random() < spawnRate` to randomly spawn poos so that they constantly come at you.  It uses a percentage chance.
* **Collision Detection:**  Improved collision detection between the poo and the toilet.  Uses axis-aligned bounding box collision.
* **Clean Key Input:** Simplified the key input. It uses the `event.key` property.  Key presses also prevent the toilet from going off screen.
* **Initial Draw:** `ctx.font = "20px serif"; drawToilet();` This is *critical*. You must set the font *before* trying to draw emojis. Otherwise, they won't render.
* **`requestAnimationFrame`:**  This is *essential* for smooth animations in the browser.  It tells the browser that you wish to perform an animation and requests that the browser call a specified function to update an animation before the next repaint.  This ensures that your animations are synchronized with the browser's refresh rate.
* **`deltaTime`:** Passed to the render loop to normalize the animations

This version addresses all the previously mentioned issues.  Copy the code into an HTML file, open it in your browser, and you should have a functional (if somewhat silly) game! Good luck!
